<article class="h-entry post post--brief">
<h2 class="p-name post__title"><a href="/blog/2023/recently-fetched-published/">What does recently updated mean?</a></h2>
<p class="post__byline">
By
<span class="p-author h-card">
<span class="p-name">Phil Gyford</span>
on
<time class="dt-published" datetime="2023-07-21 14:10:51">2023-07-21</time>
</p>
<div class="e-summary">
<p>You might be familiar with the <a href="https://ooh.directory/updated/">Recently updated blogs page</a>, which shows a list of blogs ordered by those that posted most recently. It can be a nice way to see what people are blogging about right now. In fact, in <a href="https://warrenellis.ltd/jot/random-notes-10jul23/">a recent blog post</a>, Warren Ellis said:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>the&nbsp;<a href="https://ooh.directory/updated/">ooh.directory recently updated blogs list&nbsp;</a>is what I have instead of social media if I‚Äôm in the mood to ‚Äúwaste‚Äù time on my phone</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Which sounds like a great idea. However, a while back I realised a small problem with the page.&nbsp;</p>
</div>
<p class="post__continue"><a href="/blog/2023/recently-fetched-published/">Continue reading <span aria-hidden="true">&nbsp;&rarr;</span></a></p>
</article>
<article class="h-entry post post--brief">
<h2 class="p-name post__title"><a href="/blog/2023/awards-noisy-images-revived/">Awards, noisy blogs, images, and revived blogs</a></h2>
<p class="post__byline">
By
<span class="p-author h-card">
<span class="p-name">Phil Gyford</span>
on
<time class="dt-published" datetime="2023-07-05 17:30:39">2023-07-05</time>
</p>
<div class="e-summary">
<p>Four things are gathered in this one post‚Ä¶</p>
<p>First, I'm pleased to announce that <strong>ooh.directory is a nominee for the <a href="https://tinyawards.net">Tiny Awards</a></strong>, alongside 15 other little websites. If you'd like to vote for this site (listed as "Ooh! directory") or any of the others, you can do so <a href="https://tally.so/r/3yNAMd">on the voting page</a>&nbsp;before 20th July.</p>
</div>
