<article class="h-entry post post--brief">
<h2 class="p-name post__title"><a href="/blog/2023/newsletter-blog-posts/">The newsletter will now be blog posts</a></h2>
<p class="post__byline">
By
<span class="p-author h-card">
<span class="p-name">Phil Gyford</span>
on
<time class="dt-published" datetime="2023-03-01 18:18:45">2023-03-01</time>
</p>
<div class="e-summary">
<p>I've just sent out the second issue of the email newsletter but, in a sense, it's the last issue of the email newsletter. After this, all blog posts will be sent to the newsletter, and there won't be <em>different</em> content delivered by email. You can subscribe to this blog by RSS or, now <a href="https://buttondown.email/oohdirectory">by email</a>. There's no newsletter with its own different content.</p>
</div>
<p class="post__continue"><a href="/blog/2023/newsletter-blog-posts/">Continue reading <span aria-hidden="true">&nbsp;&rarr;</span></a></p>
</article>
